overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed Statement of Work and questionnaire
  specification. The primary goal was to ensure all acceptance criteria were met
  and to identify any missing features. The agent proceeded to implement several
  critical enhancements. This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores. Detection logic for
  COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome was
  integrated into the reports, along with tailored recommendations. A dedicated
  "Resources & Next Steps" section was added, featuring placeholder outbound
  links to various sleep and mental health resources. Finally, the agent
  implemented a weighted scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS)
  to provide more accurate severity assessments. These changes involved
  modifications across data types, validation schemas, UI components, and both
  web and PDF report generation logic.
